core.conflict

Interface IConflictResolutionStrategy<T,E>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of entities that define the conflict scope of this conflict resolution strategy.
    E - The type of entities that underly the conflict incurred by the conflict source entity resolved by this conflict resolution strategy.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractConflictResolutionStrategy, AbstractExpertRenameConflictResolutionStrategy, AbstractRenameConflictResolutionStrategy, DefaultRenameAssociationConflictResolutionStrategy, DefaultRenameAttributeConflictResolutionStrategy, DefaultRenameDependencyConflictResolutionStrategy, DiscardConflictingAssociationConflictResolutionStrategy, DiscardConflictingAttributeConflictResolutionStrategy, DiscardConflictingDependencyConflictResolutionStrategy, DiscardConflictResolutionStrategy, ExpertRenameAssociationConflictResolutionStrategy, ExpertRenameAttributeConflictResolutionStrategy, ExpertRenameDependencyConflictResolutionStrategy

    public interface IConflictResolutionStrategy<T,E>
    an IConflictResolutionStrategy generic interface that defines a conflict resolution strategy.

    When a conflict is originated by a conflict source entity for a given conflict scope, it has to be resolved by a conflict resolution strategy. The resolution yields a target entity, having the same type as that of the conflict source entity (and of the entities forming its enclosing conflict scope by extension), that no longer is in a conflict state. Since a conflict might be resolved using different conflict resolution strategies, the choice of a conflict resolution strategy is dictated by whether the underlying conflicting entities share the same semantics or not.

    It must be specialized by all concrete conflict resolution strategy classes.
    Author:
    Bachar Rima
    See Also:
    AbstractConflictScope, AbstractConflictSource
